Q1: Get Character at Given Index in a String in Java

You are developing a Java program that requires extracting a character at a specific index within a given string. The index you want to access may vary, so you need a method to retrieve the character efficiently.

Write a Java program that takes a string and an index as input and returns the character at the specified index within the string.

Input : Aditya
		3
		

Test Case : 1
Expected output : Character at index 3: t
Actual output : Character at index 7: t

